{"lemma":"حَرْثُ","slug":"حَرْثُ","root":"ح.ر.ث","root_slug":"ح-ر-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَرْث","root":"حرث","pos":"N","occurrence_count":13},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7552","n7553"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AB%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to plow, to till, to cultivate","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرَثَ (ḥaraṯa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plowing, tilling, cultivation, plantation, culture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arable land, tilth","examples":[{"text":"نِسَاؤُكُمْ حَرْثٌ لَكُمْ فَأْتُوا حَرْثَكُمْ أَنَّى شِئْتُمْ وَقَدِّمُوا لِأَنْفُسِكُمْ وَاتَّقُوا اللَّهَ وَاعْلَمُوا أَنَّكُمْ مُلَاقُوهُ وَبَشِّرِ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ","english":"Your wives are a place of sowing of seed for you, so come to your place of cultivation however you wish and put forth [righteousness] for yourselves. And fear Allah and know that you will meet Him. And give good tidings to the believers."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ḥaraṯ-.\nCognate with Hebrew חרש (ħaráš)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7552","headword_ar":"حَرَثَ","root":"Hrv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarovN","text_ar":"حَرْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gained, acquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) wealth; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtrv","text_ar":"احترث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he collected"},{"kind":"text","text":"wealth. (S, A, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought, sought after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought to gain, sustenance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laboured diligently;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEiyaAlihi","text_ar":"لِعِيَالِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his family;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtrv","text_ar":"احترث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he worked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laboured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the goods of the present world, (Az, TA,) and (tropical:)  for those of the world to come. (Az, A, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuHoruvo liA=xiratika","text_ar":"اُحْرُثْ لِا=خِرَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Labour for thy good in the world to come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuHoruvo lidunoyaAka kaA^an~aka","text_ar":"اُحْرُثْ لِدُنْيَاكَ كَاَنَّكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiy$u A^abadFA","text_ar":"تَعِيشُ اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Labour for thy good in the present world as though thou wert to live for ever:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, in continuation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@Eomalo liA=xiratika kaA^an~aka tamuwtu","text_ar":"وَا@عْمَلْ لِا=خِرَتِكَ كَاَنَّكَ تَمُوتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadFA","text_ar":"غَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and work for thy good in the world to come as though thou wert to die to-morrow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harava","text_ar":"حَرَثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarovN","text_ar":"حَرْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiraAvapN","text_ar":"حِرَاثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtrv","text_ar":"احترث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cast seed upon the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) [accord. to Bd (xlii. 19), this is the primary signification: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarovN","text_ar":"حَرْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:] and the former verb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he tilled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"land, either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by sowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by planting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ploughed up"},{"kind":"text","text":"land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for sowing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ploughed"},{"kind":"text","text":"land; because the doing so is a means of gain. (Ham p. 70.) And the former verb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ploughed up"},{"kind":"text","text":"the ground"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by much walking upon it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHrv","text_ar":"احرث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also, the former verb, (L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarovN","text_ar":"حَرْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had, four wives together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Immoderatè inivit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"multùm inivit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harava A@moraA^atahu","text_ar":"حَرَثَ ا@مْرَاَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Multùm inivit mulierem suam."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, L.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, A, K,) a beast, (K,) or a camel, (IAar, TA,) or a she-camel, (IAar, S, A,) and a horse, (IAar, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHrv","text_ar":"احرث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":542},{"kind":"text","text":"A and L and TA, and in some copies of the S, in this art., and so in the S and L and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lhd","text_ar":"لهد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtrv","text_ar":"احترث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in some copies of the S in the present art.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stirred"},{"kind":"text","text":"a fire, (S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to burn up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAv","text_ar":"مِحْرَاث"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He examined, looked into, scrutinized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"investigated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) app. in an absolute sense: but accord. to some of the leading lexicologists,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he examined, looked into, scrutinized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"investigated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the book, or the Kur-án: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he studied"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Kur-án: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he studied"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Kur-án"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long, and meditated upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"it. (A, TA.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called to mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing, or an affair,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and became excited thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for ex.,] Ru-beh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waAlqawolu manosiY~N A_i*aA lamo yuHoravi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the saying is forgotten if it be not called to mind so as to produce excitement"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b10-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applied himself to the study of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfiqoh","text_ar":"الفِقْه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he learned the science so called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","Az","TA","T","Mgh","L","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n7553","headword_ar":"حَرْثٌ","root":"Hrv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gain, acquisition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xlii. 19;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariyvapN","text_ar":"حَرِيثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAy^ivu","text_ar":"حَرَايِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xlii. 19, and TA. [Accord. to Bd, in the place here referred to, this is from the same word as meaning “ seed-produce: but the reverse seems to be the case accord. to the generality of the lexicologists.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano kaAna yuriydu Harova AlA=xirapi","text_ar":"مَنْ كَانَ يُرِيدُ حَرْثَ الا=خِرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xlii. 19, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso desireth the reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the gain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the world to come."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lot, share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Worldly goods."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seed-produce:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, * TA:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is grown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised, by means of seed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of date-stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of planting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) an inf. n. used as a proper subst.: (Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwvN","text_ar":"حُرُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place ploughed for sowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoravN","text_ar":"مَحْرَثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArivu","text_ar":"مَحَارِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land prepared for sowing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in ii. 66:) and it is said to signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps because one ploughs in it. (Ham p. 70.) [Being originally an inf. n., it is also used in a pl. sense.] It is said in the Kur ii. 223,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisaA=w^ukumo HarovN lakumo","text_ar":"نِسَا=وُكُمْ حَرْثٌ لَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Your wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women, are unto you things wherein ye sow your offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) they are thus likened to places that are ploughed for sowing. (Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b6-  [And hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa Harovuka","text_ar":"كَيْفَ حَرْثُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How is thy wife?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaten track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle of a road, that is much trodden"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though ploughed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the hoofs of horses or the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ploughshare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in Richardson's Pers. Ar. and Engl. Dict., ed. by Johnson; and so, app., in the Munjid of Kr, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAbN","text_ar":"عُقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","Bd","Jel","Mgh","Msb"]}]}}